---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="HisabProx Case Study">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[68ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2 text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono">
        <span>Work</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>Case Study</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-tight">
        HisabProx
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] italic">
        "Build things that still make sense a decade later."
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Case Study Content -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-12 text-[#FAFAFA] text-base leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      
      <!-- Why We Built It -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Why We Built HisabProx</h2>
        <p>
          Freelancers frequently need to compile professional invoices for clients.
          Many existing billing services require cloud subscription accounts and collect client data.
          I built HisabProx to offer developers a private, local-first invoice editor.
          The goal was to keep invoice generation distraction-free and completely private.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- The Biggest Mistake -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">The Biggest Mistake</h2>
        <p>
          I originally integrated a remote backup sync utility.
          This required setting up database credentials and user accounts.
          It added maintenance complexity to what should have been a simple client utility.
          I removed the remote sync to ensure client data never leaves the browser environment.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- The Architecture -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">The Architecture</h2>
        <p>
          HisabProx is a static React application built with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS.
          It uses the browser local storage API to retain client and invoice datasets.
          PDF compilation is handled directly on the client side using PDFKit.
          The entire application operates offline without backend servers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Trade-offs -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Trade-offs</h2>
        <p>
          I traded automated multi-device syncing for zero server maintenance costs and total privacy.
          Users must manually export JSON backups to move records across devices.
          This design decision ensures complete data security for client invoices.
          The application requires no external database infrastructure to operate.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Lessons -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Lessons</h2>
        <p>
          The most secure and cost-effective system is the one that avoids storing data on a remote server.
          Client-side capabilities are often underutilized in modern web development.
          Local-first architectures are ideal for utility tools.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Links / GitHub -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.08)] pt-6">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Source Code</h2>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-xs font-mono">
          <a href="https://github.com/programmer-nick234/hisabprox" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[#2563EB] hover:underline">
            GitHub Repository
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- Tech Stack footer -->
    <footer class="flex flex-col gap-6 border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.08)] pt-8 mt-4 text-xs font-mono text-[#71717A]">
      <span>Technologies: TypeScript · React · Local Storage · PDFKit</span>
    </footer>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
